<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12054a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12054a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12054a"> 54(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> king of pilgrims / white sheepskin gloves</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Elle devait &ecirc;tre bien bizarre la cohue des p&egrave;lerins d&apos;autrefois. Certaines confr&eacute;ries, venant en groupes, devaient &ecirc;tre, d&apos;apr&egrave;s leurs statuts, command&eacute;es par un roi &agrave; cheval, ayant sur la t&ecirc;te une couronne d&apos;argent; chaque p&egrave;lerin &eacute;tait porteur d&apos;un javelot, avec une cocarde verte au chapeau, une bandoli&egrave;re bleuze (sic); les gants blancs de mouton &eacute;taient de rigueur. (<cite>Archives du Calvados</cite>, mai 1755; Certificats.) <br><font color="green">[It must have been a bizarre sight in those days, the crowd of pilgrims. Some confraternities, coming in by group, had statutes that said that they needed to be commanded by <mark>a king on horseback</mark>, with on his head a silver crown; each pilgrim carried a javelin, with a green cockade on the hat, a &ldquo;bleuze&rdquo; (sic) bandoleer; <mark>white sheepskin gloves</mark> were required. (<cite>Archives du Calvados</cite>, May 1755; Certificates.)]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 69n</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
